This paper deals with the security and communication challenges in a networked environment, specifically in the context of UAV surveillance. The paper discusses the optimization of network parameters such as coding rates, transmit power, and number of hops to improve the throughput and transmission reliability. The paper also considers the issues of secrecy and covert communication, which are relevant to the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT), cryptography and security (cs.CR), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
